    <h3>Priority scheduling</h3>
    <p>Each process has a priority. Highest priority runs first. Risk: <strong>starvation</strong> of low-priority processes. Solution: <strong>aging</strong>, which gradually increases priority of waiting processes.</p>

    <h3>Multilevel queues</h3>
    <p>Multiple ready queues, each with its own scheduling algorithm. Foreground processes get round-robin. Background processes get FCFS. A multilevel feedback queue lets processes move between queues based on behavior.</p>

    <h3>Metrics</h3>
    <p><strong>Turnaround time</strong> = completion time minus arrival time. <strong>Waiting time</strong> = turnaround time minus burst time. <strong>Response time</strong> = first run minus arrival time. Good schedulers minimize all three, but tradeoffs are inevitable.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; FCFS vs SJF: compare average waiting times
; Processes: (name burst-time)

(define (avg-wait-fcfs bursts)
  (define (helper bs wait total count)
    (if (null? bs)
        (/ total count)
        (helper (cdr bs) (+ wait (car bs))
                (+ total wait) (+ count 1))))
  (helper bursts 0 0 0))

(define (avg-wait-sjf bursts)
  (avg-wait-fcfs (sort bursts <)))

(define bursts '(6 2 8 3))

(display "Bursts: ") (display bursts) (newline)
(display "FCFS avg wait: ") (display (avg-wait-fcfs bursts)) (newline)
(display "SJF  avg wait: ") (display (avg-wait-sjf bursts))
; SJF always wins on average waiting time
`} />

